'''乌托邦平原'''（Utopia Planitia）是[[火星|火星]]乌托邦区一处广袤的[[平原|平原]]<ref name = "USGS_Utopia_Planitia" />，是火星{{efn| Officially, Utopia is an albedo feature.<ref name="USGS_Utopia">{{cite web|title=Utopia|work=Gazetteer of Planetary Nomenclature|publisher=[[USGS_Astrogeology_Science_Center|USGS Astrogeology Science Center]]|url=https://planetarynames.wr.usgs.gov/Feature/6259|access-date=2022-04-01|archive-date=2021-05-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210518014227/https://planetarynames.wr.usgs.gov/Feature/6259}}</ref>}}及[[太阳系|太阳系]]中公认最大的[[撞击盆地|撞击盆地]]，直径估计达3300公里<ref name="McGill1989">{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1029/JB094iB03p02753| title = Buried topography of Utopia, Mars: Persistence of a giant impact depression| journal = Journal of Geophysical Research| volume = 94| pages = 2753–2759| date = 1989-03-10| last1 = McGill | first1 = G. E. |bibcode = 1989JGR....94.2753M }}</ref>。它坐落在火星[[卡西乌斯区|卡西乌斯区]]、[[阿蒙蒂斯区|阿蒙蒂斯区]]和[[刻布壬尼亚区|刻布壬尼亚区]]之间，位于[[阿耳古瑞平原|阿耳古瑞平原]]的对跖点上，其中心坐标为{{Coord|46.7|117.5|globe:Mars}}<ref name="USGS_Utopia_Planitia">{{cite web|title=Utopia Planitia|work=Gazetteer of Planetary Nomenclature|publisher=[[USGS_Astrogeology_Science_Center|USGS Astrogeology Science Center]]|url=https://planetarynames.wr.usgs.gov/Feature/6260|access-date=2015-03-10|archive-date=2021-05-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210518045457/https://planetarynames.wr.usgs.gov/Feature/6260}}</ref>。1976年9月3日美国[[海盗2号|海盗2号]]着陆器和2021年5月14日中国[[天问一号|天问一号]]任务中[[祝融号火星车|祝融号火星车]]分别着陆在该火星区域并进行了探测<ref>{{cite web|title=China succeeds on country's first Mars landing attempt with Tianwen-1|url=https://www.nasaspaceflight.com/2021/05/china-first-mars-landing-attempt-tianwen-1/|website=nasaspaceglight.com|access-date=May 15, 2021|archive-date=2021-05-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210514165345/https://www.nasaspaceflight.com/2021/05/china-first-mars-landing-attempt-tianwen-1/}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.space.com/china-mars-mission-tianwen-1-details.html|title=China's first Mars rover Tianwen-1 launches this week. Here's what it will do.|website=Space.com|access-date=2022-04-01|archive-date=2021-05-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210519170359/https://www.space.com/china-mars-mission-tianwen-1-details.html}}</ref>。

托邦平原上的许多岩石似乎都散铺在表面，仿佛风吹走了它们下方大部分的土壤<ref>Mutch, T. et al. 1976. The Surface of Mars: The View from the Viking 2 Lander. ''Science'': 194. 1277–1283.</ref><ref>Hartmann, W. 2003. ''A Traveler's Guide to Mars''. Workman Publishing. NY NY.</ref>。上涌的地下矿物溶液在表面蒸发形成一层坚硬的表层地壳<ref>Arvidson, R. A. Binder, and K. Jones. 1976. The Surface of Mars. ''Scientific American'': 238. 76–89.</ref>，部分区域表面显示出像用冰淇淋勺挖出的[[扇形地形|扇形地形]]，这种表面被认为是由富含水冰的永久冻土层退化而成<ref>Sejourne, A. et al. 2012. Evidence of an eolian ice-rich and stratified permafrost in Utopia Planitia, Mars. Icarus. 60:248-254.</ref>。在乌托邦平原（约北纬35–50度、东经80–115度），很多特征看上去类似地球上所发现的[[冰核丘|冰核丘]]<ref>Soare, E., et al. 2019.Possible (closed system) pingo and ice-wedge/thermokarst complexes at the mid latitudes of Utopia Planitia, Mars. Icarus. https://doi.org/10.1016/j.icarus.2019.03.010</ref>。

2016年11月22日，美国宇航局报告称，在乌托邦平原地区发现了大量[[火星水文|地下冰]]。据估计，检测到的水量相当于一座[[苏必利尔湖|苏必利尔湖]]<ref name="NASA-20161122">{{cite web |author=Staff |title=Scalloped Terrain Led to Finding of Buried Ice on Mars |url=http://photojournal.jpl.nasa.gov/catalog/PIA21136 |date=November 22, 2016 |work=[[NASA|NASA]] |access-date=November 23, 2016 |archive-date=2018-12-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181226060804/https://photojournal.jpl.nasa.gov/catalog/PIA21136%20 }}</ref><ref name="Register-2016">{{cite web |url=https://www.theregister.co.uk/2016/11/22/nasa_finds_ice_under_martian_surface/ |title=Lake of frozen water the size of New Mexico found on Mars – NASA |publisher=The Register |date=November 22, 2016 |access-date=November 23, 2016 |archive-date=2018-12-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181226060808/https://www.theregister.co.uk/2016/11/22/nasa_finds_ice_under_martian_surface/%20 }}</ref><ref name="NASA-20161122jpl">{{cite web |url=http://www.jpl.nasa.gov/news/news.php?release=2016-299 |title=Mars Ice Deposit Holds as Much Water as Lake Superior |publisher=NASA |date=November 22, 2016 |access-date=November 23, 2016 |archive-date=2018-12-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181226060807/https://www.jpl.nasa.gov/news/ }}</ref>。
